entry.def: A warm-up is something that prepares you for an activity or event, usually because it is a short practice or example of what the activity or event will involve.

example.ex: The exercises can be fun and a good warm-up for the latter part of the programme...
example.tran: 这些练习很有趣，而且为该课程后面的部分做了很好的铺垫。

example.ex: The criticism was merely a warm-up for what is being prepared for the finance minister...
example.tran: 对于财政部长即将面临的困境而言，这些批评只是个小小的开始。
